  "Father and son Kapil & Rahul Bhatia get the bulk of their wealth from  InterGlobe Aviation, which owns budget carrier IndiGo, India's biggest airline.",
  "IndiGo, which was cofounded with billionaire airline veteran Rakesh Gangwal in 2006, has a 60% domestic market share. ",
